Sentencas: Molten alloys with 50-mol% In-Sb, Sn-Sb, Sb-Bi, and Sb-Pb were examined as anodes for solid oxide fuel cells at 973 K.
Titulo: Characteristics of Molten Alloys as Anodes in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The cells were operated in the battery mode, without added fuel, in order to understand the oxidation characteristics of these alloys at electrolyte interfaces.
Titulo: Characteristics of Molten Alloys as Anodes in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Cells using 50-mol% In-Sb and Sn-Sb mixtures exhibited open-circuit voltages (OCV) of 1.0 and 0.93 V, values that are identical to that of cell with pure In and Sn respectively.
Titulo: Characteristics of Molten Alloys as Anodes in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Also similar to the pure In and Sn anodes, the impedances of these cells were initially low but increased dramatically after drawing a small amount of charge, implying formation of In(2)O(3) and SnO(2) layers at the electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Characteristics of Molten Alloys as Anodes in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The 50-mol% Sb-Bi cell had an OCV of 0.73 V initially, close to the OCV observed with pure Sb.
Titulo: Characteristics of Molten Alloys as Anodes in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The OCV remained constant until a charge identical to that required for oxidation of all the Sb had been passed, after which the OCV dropped to 0.43 V, similar to the value for pure Bi.
Titulo: Characteristics of Molten Alloys as Anodes in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: SEM analysis of the cell after conversion of the Sb showed two distinct phases, with metallic Bi at the bottom and Sb(2)O(3) at the top.
Titulo: Characteristics of Molten Alloys as Anodes in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical oxidation of 50-mol% Sb-Pb alloys exhibited an OCV that changed continuously with conversion, from 0.73 V initially to 0.67 V following the addition of charge corresponding to oxidation of 120% the Sb.
Titulo: Characteristics of Molten Alloys as Anodes in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The total cell impedance remained low for this entire period.
Titulo: Characteristics of Molten Alloys as Anodes in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: EDS measurements on the sectioned Sb-Pb cell suggested that both Sb and Pb were oxidized simultaneously to form a mixed oxide of Pb and Sb. (C) 2011 The Electrochemical Society.
Titulo: Characteristics of Molten Alloys as Anodes in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
